def: The daughter of Njörd, aud goddess of love and beauty; theScandinavian Venus; -- in Teutonic myths confounded with Frigga, butin Scandinavian, distinct. [Written also Frea, Fraying, and Ereyja.]
The habit or power of eating all kinds of food.
An ericaceous shrub (Leucothoë acuminata) of the southernUnited States, from the wood of which pipe bowls are made.
A variety of allanite from Sweden supposed to contain wasium.
The state of being inaquate. [Obs.] Bp. Gardiner.
Eternal; everlasting. [Obs.] -- Ev`i*ter"nal*ly, adv. Bp. Hall.
One versed in, or who writes on, mythology or myths.
Quality or state of being weakish.
